{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLIN nods: everybody does.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: YOUNG COLIN
{DIALOGUE}: Thank you.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pushes out with the bags of groceries.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The PROPRIETOR can do shit about it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: YOUNG COSTELLO watches YOUNG COLIN go off down a slummy street.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. A CHURCH. MORNING. 1985-ISH
