{DIALOGUE}: The slug enters the skull by forming a small entrance hole.
{DIALOGUE}: Blood and brain matter is ejected backwards from this hole.
{DIALOGUE}: The bullet, which may expand, fragment or tumble, then passes through the brain...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLIN writes.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. FIRING RANGE. DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: POLICE TRAINEES ON A FIRING RANGE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As we go along the line we see COLIN, firing dry and then speed-changing a clip in a BERETTA 92F.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is a perfect trainee.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. A TRAINING FIELD. DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: STATE POLICE TRAINEES standing in a pissing rain, a DI yelling at them OS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLIN is staring forward.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: RAIN streaming down his face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His opinion on the experience is not decipherable.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ad libs: "Sir, yes, sir."
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. THE BOSTON COMMON. DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Guys we recognize from the previous shots at the State Police Academy (wearing Statie t-shirts), including COLIN and BARRIGAN, are playing rugby against some FIREFIGHTERS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Very rough game.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The game breaks up with each group giving each other the finger.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FIREFIGHTERS are moving away triumphantly.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLIN
{DIALOGUE}: Fucking firemen are getting pussy for the first time in the history of fire.
{DIALOGUE}: Or pussy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLIN sits on a bench looking at THE GOLD DOME OF BEACON HILL.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The terraces of fine townhouses.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Aqueous golden light behind.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Misty golden beauty.
