{DIALOGUE}: Whoa, let's say you have no idea and leave it there.
{DIALOGUE}: No idea.
{DIALOGUE}: Zip, none.
{DIALOGUE}: If you had an idea about what we do we would not be good at what we do.
{DIALOGUE}: We would be cunts.
{DIALOGUE}: Are you calling us cunts?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BILLY wouldn't normally take crap from this guy; but he does.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's openly intrigued by the situation.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dignam is staring at him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BILLY looks evenly at QUEENAN.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: QUEENAN
{META_DATA}: (not looking up from papers)
{DIALOGUE}: Staff Sergeant Dignam has a style of his own.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm afraid we all have to deal with it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SGT. DIGNAM
{META_DATA}: (getting to business, hard)
{DIALOGUE}: You have family connections down in Southie.
{DIALOGUE}: Through your father.
{DIALOGUE}: Tell us about your uncle Jackie.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILLY
{DIALOGUE}: Uncle Jackie was a carpet layer for Jordan Marsh.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SGT. DIGNAM
{DIALOGUE}: Uncle Jackie was a small-time bookie who tended bar at the Vets in Somerville.
{META_DATA}: (MORE)
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 13.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED: (2)
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SGT. DIGNAM (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: He got popped by Nicastro in '95.
{DIALOGUE}: They found his body out by the airport.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BILLY says slowly:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILLY
{DIALOGUE}: That's right.
{META_DATA}: (tightly)
{DIALOGUE}: I remember his funeral.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SGT. DIGNAM
{META_DATA}: (cruelly)
{DIALOGUE}: Closed casket?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILLY
{DIALOGUE}: That's right.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SGT. DIGNAM
{DIALOGUE}: You tell anybody at Deerfield - that is, before you got kicked out for whaling on a gym teacher with a folding chair - you had an uncle met his demise like that?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BILLY says nothing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Eyes luminous.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SGT. DIGNAM (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: I got a question.
{DIALOGUE}: How fucked up are you?
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. CORRIDOR POLICE BUILDING. DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLIN, in his good suit, moves along the hall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He owns the building.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks into offices.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is looking at his future.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: From one room BARRIGAN (still working in uniform) gives him the thumbs up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLIN gets a coffee.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks at a secretary's ass.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Caught at it, he smiles beautifully.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She smiles back.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BARRIGAN
{DIALOGUE}: What you got?
{META_DATA}: (with admiration and envy)
{DIALOGUE}: "Staff Sergeant".
{DIALOGUE}: In four years you're a sergeant.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLIN
{DIALOGUE}: SIU.
{DIALOGUE}: What a country.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BARRIGAN
{META_DATA}: (after a beat)
{DIALOGUE}: Perfect.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 14.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Meaning to some extent "Perfect for a dick like you".
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: This is how friends come apart.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BARRIGAN is unable to continue his pose of congratulation.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLIN (close on Colin) is on to him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLIN
{DIALOGUE}: I don't mind going it alone.
{DIALOGUE}: If you could go it alone you might get somewhere yourself.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BARRIGAN
{DIALOGUE}: We're cops.
{DIALOGUE}: This isn't "somewhere".
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLIN
{DIALOGUE}: I know you're a worker.
