{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. HUNTINGTON AVENUE. LATE DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A TROLLEY goes past.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HOSPITAL HILL, above the trolley line, is sinister, quiet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HOSPITAL at the top like a malign fortress, above rows of endlessly repeated condominiums.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BILLY CROSSES from the Trolley stop, desperately, an angry young man at his life's turning point.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. A HOSPITAL ROOM. LATER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BILLY'S MOTHER lies as if floating in her bed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tubes, lights.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A bald head on a barely-dented pillow.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She is a cancer patient in a coma, weighing possibly 80 lbs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gasping for air.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her airways are cleared with a suction tube.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BILLY sits watching as the tube goes in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BILLY sits looking at her.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. THE HOSPITAL CORRIDOR. LATER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BILLY is leaning against a wall.
