{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LAZIO, the Fed, comes in and sits down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With folders, pencil.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 25.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SGT. DIGNAM (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Somebody, as you may already know, stole one hundred microprocessors from the Mass Processor Corp out Route 128.
{DIALOGUE}: They're the kind of processors they put into computers that can put a cruise missile up the ass of a camel from the other side of the planet.
{DIALOGUE}: That's what they do out there on "America's Technology Highway".
{DIALOGUE}: Worth a hundred grand apiece.
{DIALOGUE}: Guy worked for the company two months walked out the door with a box of processors on Tuesday, has a ticket booked for Florida on Wednesday, but on Thursday he gets found in a dumpster.
{DIALOGUE}: You know where this dirt ball started his life?
{DIALOGUE}: Southie projects.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLIN
{DIALOGUE}: What was his name?
{DIALOGUE}: The, ah, departed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SGT. DIGNAM
{DIALOGUE}: Myles Kennefick.
{DIALOGUE}: Got the job with a forged UMass transcript.
{DIALOGUE}: UMass Boston, which incidentally happens to be in...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LAZIO
{DIALOGUE}: South Boston?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SGT. DIGNAM
{DIALOGUE}: Who forged your transcript, dickhead?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLIN
{DIALOGUE}: I know that guy.
{DIALOGUE}: His father runs the Hibernian Liquor Mart.
{DIALOGUE}: Kennefick's.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELLERBY
{DIALOGUE}: We are not here to solve the "Case of the Dead Scumbag".
{DIALOGUE}: We are here to nail Costello.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLIN stands down, embarrassed.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 26.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED: (2)
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SGT. DIGNAM
{DIALOGUE}: We got a guy says that he hears Costello is moving the processors to China...that he set up the whole fuckin' job and popped Kennefick.
{META_DATA}: (LAZIO is writing, lawyerish.)
{DIALOGUE}: You don't want to miss it if Costello takes a dump.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELLERBY
{DIALOGUE}: We'd miss less if your informants were available to us, and of course to the FBI (Bureau)...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LAZIO
{DIALOGUE}: Without asking for details, do you have anyone in with Costello presently?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SGT. DIGNAM
{DIALOGUE}: Maybe.
{DIALOGUE}: Maybe not.
{DIALOGUE}: Maybe fuck yourself.
{DIALOGUE}: My theory on Feds is they're like mushrooms.
{DIALOGUE}: Feed 'em shit and keep in the dark.
{DIALOGUE}: You girls have a nice day.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. A STREET OF TENEMENTS IN SOUTHIE. DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BILLY steps off a bus at a corner.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He goes up to a house, and knocks on the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A Southie hag answers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On an oxygen cylinder, smoking.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILLY'S AUNT
{DIALOGUE}: Billy?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BILLY nods.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILLY
{DIALOGUE}: Aunt Cathy?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His aunt takes her cigarette out of her mouth and then embraces him fiercely.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BILLY takes it like the imposter he is.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But he might well love his aunt.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILLY'S AUNT
{DIALOGUE}: Good to see you.
{DIALOGUE}: Good to see you.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BILLY'S AUNT'S KITCHEN. DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BILLY is eating soup.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 27.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILLY'S AUNT
{DIALOGUE}: They said you were in the Staties, I couldn't believe it.
