{META_DATA}: (affably to Billy)
{DIALOGUE}: You workin'?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILLY
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 28.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. THE PORCH OF THE THREE-DECKER. LATER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sean and BILLY are still drinking beer.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SEAN
{DIALOGUE}: When did I see you after that?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILLY
{DIALOGUE}: Not for a long time.
{DIALOGUE}: Down the cape after Rose's wedding.
{DIALOGUE}: I think.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SEAN
{DIALOGUE}: Fuck, oh shit.
{DIALOGUE}: I remember that, dude.
{DIALOGUE}: I had that fuckin' buck knife, right, and I cut all the brass numbas off the doors at the hotel.
{DIALOGUE}: I was trippin'...All of them.
{DIALOGUE}: That was a night.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sean looks deflated.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILLY
