{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BILLY is finishing his breakfast.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Watching.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He goes over.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The two GUINEAS are amazed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: [Dialog on separate document].
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Billy is finishing his breakfast.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Watching.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He goes over....
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILLY
{DIALOGUE}: You guys from Providence?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The GUINEAS look at him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The younger one moves to intervene.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BILLY smiles and destroys them both.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Maniacal violence.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The biggest beatdown in gangster movie history--and obviously that's saying something.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In the course of the beat-down Billy breaks his left hand--a "boxer's fracture".
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BILLY stands over his victims, breathing hard, holding his broken hand.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PROPRIETOR
{DIALOGUE}: What have you done to my place!
{DIALOGUE}: Get out of here.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BILLY goes.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. EMERGENCY ROOM. NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BILLY, unlit cigarette in his mouth, is having his hand wrapped in plaster by a lady doctor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In another life he might have dated her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Not in this one.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. FRENCH RESTAURANT. NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A romantic restaurant.
