{DIALOGUE}: Yes I do.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MADOLYN
{DIALOGUE}: If you actually do I'll see you again.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLIN
{DIALOGUE}: Who says I want to see you again?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MADOLYN
{META_DATA}: (concerned, perhaps unexpectedly)
{DIALOGUE}: Don't you?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLIN
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, course I do.
{META_DATA}: (a beat)
{DIALOGUE}: What Freud said about the Irish is We're the only people impervious to psychoanalysis.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MADOLYN is impressed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLIN (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Tough luck for you with a client list of Mick cops, isn't it.
{DIALOGUE}: "Opening up"?
{DIALOGUE}: Good luck to you.
