{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLIN (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Why do you do it?
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 39.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED: (3)
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MADOLYN
{DIALOGUE}: Some people do get better.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLIN takes it seriously; admires it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLIN
{DIALOGUE}: Fair enough.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MADOLYN
{DIALOGUE}: Sometimes, though, I want people to forget about their personal bullshit and do their jobs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Unsaid: Like I do.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLIN
{DIALOGUE}: Including the criminals?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MADOLYN
{DIALOGUE}: If they don't do their jobs you don't have one.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLIN
{DIALOGUE}: Me?
{DIALOGUE}: I'd just arrest innocent people.
{DIALOGUE}: I'll arrest you right now.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MADOLYN
{DIALOGUE}: You're trouble.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLIN
{DIALOGUE}: You don't know the half of it.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. A HORRIBLE BAR IN SOUTHIE. NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A slow night.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BILLY IS AT THE BAR bent over a glass of cranberry juice.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The women available are two CRONES.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: [Dialog on separate document].
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Stark contrast to COLIN'S EVENING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A BOOKMAKER on the phone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BILLY, by the glances of people looking at him, has made his bones.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's treated with respect.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His hand and wrist in a cast.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Out of nowhere (though Billy is aware conversation has stopped he does not look around)...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COSTELLO sits down beside him AT THE BAR.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BILLY observes:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MISTER FRENCH sitting down at a far table.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Watching.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Covering the room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COSTELLO is brought a glass of water by the silent bartender.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No sound whatsoever in the bar.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 40.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They say nothing, look at each other.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BILLY notices DELAHUNT and FITZY, entering.
