{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILLY
{DIALOGUE}: Three o'clock.
{DIALOGUE}: Where Queenan died.
{DIALOGUE}: You keep your cell on.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLIN goes to the bedroom door and tries it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Locked.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He knocks.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No answer.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLIN
{DIALOGUE}: Did we not talk about this?
{DIALOGUE}: This is my job.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's over.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He starts to punch the door, and then does not.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. COMMERCIAL BUILDING. DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLIN comes along and walks into the lobby.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is not looking for a tail...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. COMMERCIAL BUILDING ROOFTOP. DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLIN looks out through the door, no gun drawn, but very much a cop clearing his corners.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He steps out and--BILLY takes him from behind the door, his only blind side, and grabs the back of his collar and crams a pistol into the bottom of his skull.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILLY
{DIALOGUE}: Get your hands up.
{DIALOGUE}: Hands.
{DIALOGUE}: Hands.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLIN
{DIALOGUE}: Put the fuckin' gun down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BILLY turns Colin around and puts the pistol to Colin's forehead, hard enough to break the skin.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He takes out Colin's belt gun and puts it in his pocket.
{META_DATA}: (Billy screams "hands!"
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: at Colin every time he makes a move).
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLIN (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: I came here to talk some fucking sense to you.
{DIALOGUE}: You get a hold of yourself and put down the fuckin' firearm and act professional and I can get you your money.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILLY
{META_DATA}: (turning him around)
{DIALOGUE}: What did you say?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLIN
{DIALOGUE}: I can get you your...
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 147.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BILLY cracks him across the jaw with the gun.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLIN goes down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLIN is drooling blood, his bell rung, one eye open.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Billy throws away Colin's ankle gun.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLIN (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (spitting teeth)
{DIALOGUE}: Fuck, shit...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILLY
{META_DATA}: (going for Colin's cuffs)
{DIALOGUE}: You didn't come here to talk, you fuckin' maggot, you came here to get arrested.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLIN
{DIALOGUE}: Arrested?
{DIALOGUE}: Arrested for what.
{META_DATA}: (as BILLY cuffs him)
{DIALOGUE}: So you got tapes of what?
{DIALOGUE}: Costello was my informant.
{DIALOGUE}: I was his rat?
{DIALOGUE}: Fuck you.
{DIALOGUE}: Prove it.
{DIALOGUE}: I say he was my informant.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILLY
{DIALOGUE}: Get up and shut your fuckin' mouth.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLIN
{DIALOGUE}: What is this, a citizen's arrest?
{DIALOGUE}: Blow me, prick.
{DIALOGUE}: Only one of us is a cop, here, Bill.
{DIALOGUE}: Nobody knows who you are.
{DIALOGUE}: Nobody knows who you are.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILLY
{DIALOGUE}: Would you shut the fuck up.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLIN
{DIALOGUE}: I'm a sergeant in the Mass.
{DIALOGUE}: State Police.
{DIALOGUE}: Who the fuck are you?
{DIALOGUE}: Nobody.
