{META_DATA}: (BROWN wavers)
{DIALOGUE}: You fuckin' know who I am.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm taking him downstairs now.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BROWN, weapon ready, follows into the elevator lobby.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. ELEVATOR LOBBY/ELEVATOR. DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BILLY moves COLIN into the elevator and as the doors close looks back at BROWN, still in a Mexican stand-off.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLIN, nose broken, blood masking his face.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLIN
{DIALOGUE}: I can't wait for you to try to explain this to a Suffolk County grand jury.
{DIALOGUE}: This is gonna be fun.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 150.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The indicator ticks.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Down, down, down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Colin sobs.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLIN (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Just fucking kill me.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BILLY
{DIALOGUE}: I am killing you.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The doors open and for a frozen moment BILLY, holding the gun on COLIN, stares out of the car.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A LOUD BANG.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BILLY is shot through the head.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BLOOD sprays the walls, and COLIN is hit by flying blood and matter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BILLY falls, crumpled, on his face, half in and half out of the elevator.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The doors try to close...open...COLIN, covered with blood, looks up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BARRIGAN lowers his pistol.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLIN slumps, covered with blood.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BARRIGAN uncuffs him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLIN feels his wrists.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BARRIGAN picks up BILLY'S gun.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The other elevator doors open and BROWN emerges.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks into the bloody elevator and down at the dead man.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BROWN
{META_DATA}: (holstering his gun)
{DIALOGUE}: Shit...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BARRIGAN raises BILLY'S GUN and shoots BROWN in the head.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLIN stares at him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BARRIGAN
{DIALOGUE}: Did you think you were the only one he had?
{DIALOGUE}: Costello was going to sell us to the FBI.
{DIALOGUE}: It's you and me now.
{DIALOGUE}: We have to take care of each other.
{DIALOGUE}: You understand?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLIN
{DIALOGUE}: All right.
{DIALOGUE}: Give me that.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BARRIGAN casually hands COLIN BILLY'S GUN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLIN presses the gun against BARRIGAN's forehead and fires.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. THE COMMERCIAL BUILDING. DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: POLICE TAPE, plenty of cars.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Three corpses being loaded onto ambulances.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLIN, hands free, is drinking coffee from a paper cup, being checked out by a doctor.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. POLICE HQ/CONFERENCE ROOM - NOT MUCH LATER
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 151.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLIN has been cleaned up a little by paramedics.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's maybe had his lip stitched, but he's still wearing his bloody clothes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLIN
{DIALOGUE}: At that time, Trooper Barrigan, who I now understand to have been Francis Costello's informer in SIU, intercepted us in the lobby and shot Trooper William Costigan once in the head.
{META_DATA}: (drinks water)
{DIALOGUE}: At that time Barrigan retrieved Trooper Costigan's undercover weapon and shot Trooper Brown as he was approaching our location.
{DIALOGUE}: I attempted to subdue Trooper Barrigan and in the ensuing struggle was struck several times with the Walther pistol.
{DIALOGUE}: I was able to wrestle the weapon away, at which time Barrigan drew his own weapon and took aim at me.
{DIALOGUE}: I was able to get off a single shot, striking Barrigan in the head.
{DIALOGUE}: I then checked for vital signs of Troopers Brown and Costigan and discovered that they had expired.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLIN looks up, eyes clear, perfectly believable.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As we transition to the FUNERAL...bagpipes coming up.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLIN (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: I'd like to go on record that I am recommending Trooper William Costigan for the Medal of Merit.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ON SOUND
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BAGPIPES (Something like"Cross of Fire") as we DISSOLVE TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. CEMETERY. DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BILLY'S GRAVESITE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The same cemetery as his mother is buried in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: UNIFORMED POLICEMEN (not only State, but MDC, the way they do it, for "brother officers"), saluting.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MADOLYN is at the gravesite, dry-eyed though in, distinctly apart from COLIN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks at her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She looks away from him, apparently forever.
{META_DATA}: (CONTINUED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 152.
{META_DATA}: CONTINUED:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLIN squares off: his job in the world is to get ahead.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A salute is fired with rifles.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But later...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLIN and MADOLYN are walking through the graves.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLIN
{DIALOGUE}: What about the baby?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She moves away from him without answering.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MADOLYN walks out through the cemetery gates.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLIN hesitates.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. THE STAIRWAY OF COLIN'S APARTMENT. EVENING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLIN has a bag of expensive groceries and wine.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Living the Beacon Hill dream.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He climbs the steps slowly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He nods to a neighbor, an old lady coming down with her dog (who incidentally will never accept him as a neighbor, and COLIN briefly seems aware of this).
{META_DATA}: (Don't be afraid to get a bit French here)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He gets to his door, and starts to cry, and nearly crumples.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But he gets the door open.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks up and sees a gun.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Behind it, stepping fast out of the shadows, DIGNAM.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Avenging a guy he didn't even like, because it's the right thing to do.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COLIN looks down and sees that Dignam has plastic hospital boots on his feet.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COLIN
{META_DATA}: (accepting it, sort of, but only in a COLIN way)
{DIALOGUE}: OK.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DIGNAM fires.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Flash groceries fall all over the floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DIGNAM'S FEET step over COLIN's body, crushing one of a half dozen croissants, and DIGNAM goes down the expensive staircase, leaving the door to the apartment open.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The strangest thing happens: a rat emerges and begins to eat the dead man's croissants.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The rat hears something and runs so it's not in the shot when it
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FREEZES.
